---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const description = "Learn about our classical Lutheran approach to education at Christ Classical Academy, combining timeless educational methods with Lutheran doctrine.";
const image = "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1456513080510-7bf3a84b82f8?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1073&q=80";
---

<Layout 
  title="Our Approach" 
  description={description}
  image={image}
>
  <section class="bg-hunter-green text-white py-16">
    <div class="container mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-6 font-serif">Our Classical Lutheran Approach</h1>
      <p class="text-xl max-w-3xl">
        A School Rooted in Tradition, Truth, and Excellence
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  
  <section class="py-12 bg-white">
    <div class="container mx-auto">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-slate-50 p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-hunter-green font-serif">The "Marks of a Classical Lutheran School"</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
            The "Marks of a Classical Lutheran School" outline the essential characteristics that define a school committed to both classical education and Lutheran doctrine. These guiding principles ensure schools provide a holistic education rooted in Christian faith and classical learning traditions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-12">
          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Christ-Centered Mission</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">The school's mission is deeply rooted in the Gospel of Jesus Christ, influencing all aspects of its educational endeavors.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Confessional Foundation</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">A clear articulation of faith commitment is present in the school's foundational documents, ensuring alignment with Lutheran teachings.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Integrated Christian Worldview</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">The curriculum and instructional programs are unified by a Christian perspective, seamlessly blending faith with learning across all subjects.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Centrality of Catechesis</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Teaching the faith through catechesis is a core component at every grade level, fostering a deep understanding of Christian doctrine.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Historic Liturgy and Hymnody</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">The school embraces and teaches traditional liturgical practices and hymns, enriching the worship life and spiritual formation of students.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Commitment to Classical Education</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Adopting a classical approach, the school emphasizes the liberal arts, guiding students through the trivium (grammar, logic, rhetoric) and quadrivium (arithmetic, geometry, music, astronomy) to cultivate critical thinking and articulate expression.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Latin Instruction</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Latin is introduced, even in early grades, to enhance linguistic skills and provide a foundation for learning other languages.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Great Books Curriculum</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Students engage with the seminal works of Western civilization, fostering an appreciation for enduring ideas and cultural heritage.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Faculty Development</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">Educators are dedicated to continuous learning, deepening their understanding of both classical education methodologies and Lutheran theology.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Structured Governance</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">The school maintains clear policies and responsibilities for all members of its community, reflecting God's established orders of creation and ensuring a harmonious environment.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-royal-purple text-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 font-serif">A School Rooted in Tradition, Truth, and Excellence</h2>
          <p class="text-lg mb-6">
            You want a school that doesn't water down education or faith. A school that honors the wisdom of the past while preparing children for the future. A school that doesn't chase modern trends but instead forms strong, capable young men and women grounded in truth. A Classical Lutheran School is built for families like yours.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Faith That Stands the Test of Time</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">No feel-good fluff, no watered-down theology. We teach historic, biblical Christianity—the faith of the early church, confessed and practiced for centuries.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">A Rich and Meaningful Worship Life</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Students participate in reverent, historic Christian worship, learning hymns and liturgy that connect them to generations of believers.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Education That Forms the Whole Person</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">We use the classical model of learning, which has trained the greatest minds in history to think critically, speak clearly, and pursue truth.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">A Christian Worldview in Every Subject</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Math, science, literature, and history aren't just neutral topics—they reveal God's design, order, and purpose in creation.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Latin as the Language of History and Precision</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Mastering Latin strengthens thinking, unlocks Western civilization, and deepens students' connection to the great Christian tradition.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="bg-slate-50 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-hunter-green">Strong, Disciplined Teachers</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700">Our educators are serious about their faith, committed to their craft, and dedicated to forming strong, virtuous students.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  /* Ensure the timeline line extends fully */
  .relative.space-y-8 {
    padding-top: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Smooth transitions for hover effects */
  .group {
    transition: all 300ms ease-in-out;
  }

  /* Enhanced dot styling */
  .rounded-full {
    transition: all 300ms ease-in-out;
  }

  .group:hover .rounded-full {
    transform: scale(1.2) translateX(-50%);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(42, 78, 56, 0.2);
  }

  /* Mobile timeline adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 767px) {
    .ml-12 {
      margin-left: 3rem;
    }
  }
</style>